(1)
The functions of the
Institute
are to—
(a)
conduct medical examinations for occupational health and safety purposes;
(b)
investigate and detect occupational diseases at workplaces;
(c)
set and maintain standards for the protection of the health and safety of employees at workplaces;
(d)
provide occupational laboratory service;
(e)
promote studies and carry out investigations and research on occupational health and safety;
(f)
prepare and maintain statistics on
employee
’s morbidity and mortality;
(g)
facilitate the conduct of health risk assessments and occupational hygiene surveys in workplaces in order to quantify the level of risks and advise on control measures;
(h)
promote awareness and educational programmes relating to occupational health and safety;
(i)
collaborate with any registered training institution or scientific body to develop human capital for occupational health and safety;
(j)
advise the Minister on matters relating to occupational health and safety;
(k)
collaborate with other government agencies and relevant authorities on matters relating to occupational health and safety;
(l)
monitor and enforce compliance with this Act; and
(m)
perform any other functions necessary for the purposes of this Act.

